Rating: 3
Definitely 3 1/2 stars! I made adjustments based on other notes here: 1- used sauteed red onion rather than green. used green peas rather than beans (trying to use what I had in the house). 2-added 1 chopped carrot, 2 stalks chopped celery and 1/2 cup chopped red bell pepper. 3- used vegan mayo rather than regular (way less fat). only used 1/2 cup. Thoughts: The additional veggies were necessary--next time I'll add even more. I will also cut the pasta to 8 oz from 12 oz. Both my partner and I were incredibly pleased with the results (especially considering how little work it is). More than likely, this will become a regular dinner. And yes, there is definitely enough for a lunch or two left over!

