Easy and delicious. I added fresh basil and diced celery. One reviewer said that balsamic vinegar made the dressing brown; the solution is to use white balsamic vinegar. Stop & Shop carries it so not a rare item.

Rating: 3
I just made this salad for dinner tonight. It tastes terrific. Of course, I made some changes. First, I used only 1/2 cup mayo and 1 TBSP of balsamic. I added those a bit at a time, and that amount seemed right -- light and not overpowering. Second, I had no green onions, so I used a bit of diced red onion. Both would work. Third, I had no celery salt, so I used regular salt and added one stalk of chopped celery. Finally, I have lots of basil in the garden, so I added about 1/3 cup chopped. My main recommendation here is to go light on the dressing and add fresh herbs to brighten the flavor.

